## Important Rules

- **No real orders. Ever.** This skill emits paper trades. Live trading is gated separately.
- **The Divergence Report is the artifact.** Without it, the paper session is data without a decision.
- **Hard gates on inputs.** Strategy spec + risk engine + reliable backtest, all required. No skipping.
- **Realistic execution is the whole point.** A paper session that fills at theoretical mid is worse than no paper session, because it gives false confidence. Use the broker profile or a real sandbox.
- **Cumulative drift > 3σ pauses the session.** Don't grind through a clearly diverging session; investigate.
- **Recommendation is one of five.** Forced choice on the report. "Looks fine" is not an option.
